<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1827,2031]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,325,1827,1852]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<typeStatus box="[151,210,1828,1851]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Type</typeStatus>
material.
</emphasis>
The illustrated 
<typeStatus box="[501,549,1828,1851]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">type</typeStatus>
(note on label accompanying specimen), 
<date box="[1017,1086,1827,1851]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2011-10-04">
<number box="[1017,1044,1827,1851]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="11.0">11</number>
x 
<quantity box="[1072,1139,1827,1851]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
</date>
, is in RBINS/MT/ 
<number box="[1348,1433,1827,1852]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="524919.0">524919</number>
. It was not examined; instead, high quality photographs were provided by the museum that are reproduced in Pl. 
<number box="[1415,1431,1863,1887]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,223,1899,1924]" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="66.[151,188,1159,1181]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,375,1146]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[151,1436,375,1146]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="Fig. 1: ventral, lateral &amp; dorsal views; Fig. 2: enlarged view of protoconch (not to scale); Fig. 3: apical view, V = varix, L = edge of outer lip." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263325/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[208,223,1899,1923]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. Inasmuch as this specimen is the illustrated 
<typeStatus box="[774,825,1900,1923]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">type</typeStatus>
, it is here declared the 
<typeStatus box="[1117,1223,1899,1924]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The existence of 
<typeStatus box="[151,313,1934,1959]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
is surmised from Dautzenberg’s list of stations at which the species was reportedly taken. Dautzenberg’s original illustration is reproduced in Pl. 
<number box="[796,812,1971,1995]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
, Fig. 
<number box="[884,898,1971,1995]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="4.0">4</number>
and differs principally in the number of ribs, probably a liberty taken by the artist.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263301/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" targetBox="[242,1315,195,1773]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1812,2034]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
