<taxonomicName authority="Dautzenberg, 1900" authorityName="Dautzenberg" authorityYear="1900" box="[267,723,1812,1834]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Agladrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rhodochroa">
<emphasis box="[267,503,1812,1834]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Agladrillia rhodochroa</emphasis>
(Dautzenberg, 1900)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[733,868,1813,1834]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Upper panel</emphasis>
. Fig. 1: lectotype, Rio Hacha, Guajira Dept., Colombia (RBINS/MT/524919), ventral, lateral &amp; dorsal views. Images by Yves Barett, © RBINS, and courtesy of Thierry Backeljau. Figs. 2–3: same specimen in Fig. 5. Fig. 2: enlarged view of protoconch (not to scale); Fig. 3: apical view, V = varix, L = edge of outer lip. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[291,437,1913,1934]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Lower panel.</emphasis>
Fig. 4: reproduction of Dautzenberg (1900: pl. 9, fig. 3); Figs. 5–6: Tayrona National Park, Colombia (author’s coll.); Fig. 7: Cartagena, Bolivar Dept., Colombia (USNM 900073); Figs. 8–10: Bahia Concha, Magdalena Dept., Colombia (P. Stahlschmidt coll.); Figs. 11–12: Punta de Betin, Santa Marta, Magdalena Dept., Colombia (P. Stahlschmidt coll.).
</paragraph>
</caption>
